Instructions for Running the Bitaxe Temperature Monitor & Auto-Tuner on Linux at Boot

To have the Bitaxe Temperature Monitor & Auto-Tuner start automatically at system boot on a Linux machine, follow one of these methods

Enable and Start the Service
Run the following commands:

  sudo systemctl daemon-reload
  sudo systemctl enable bitaxe-autotuner
  sudo systemctl start bitaxe-autotuner

To verify that the script is running:
  sudo systemctl status bitaxe-autotuner

If needed, restart the service:

  sudo systemctl restart bitaxe-autotuner

To stop it:

  sudo systemctl stop bitaxe-autotuner

Now, the Bitaxe Auto-Tuner will start automatically when your Linux machine boots.
